					<description><![CDATA[<p>Helsing Raises $1.8B to Strengthen European Defence AI The company has raised a 1.8 billion dollar funding amount at series E. In order to fasten their work on their ai</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/helsing-raises-1-8b-defence-ai-platforms/" data-wpel-link="internal">Helsing Raises $1.8B to Expand European Defence AI Platforms</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Helsing Raises $1.8B to Strengthen European Defence AI</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company has raised a 1.8 billion dollar funding amount at series E. In order to fasten their work on their ai driven platforms designed for the military purpose, defence tech company Helsing announced today. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">With this funding the Munich company is now priced at 18 billion dollars. The company thus stands as one of Europe’s most valued defence firms in terms of market cap. The fundraising series was headed by Dragoneer Investment Group andLightspeed Venture Partners came out as the co lead investor in the same. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The investment saw participation from few fresh investors, like Disruptive,ICONIQ, Goldman Sachs Alternatives, JPMorgan Chase, CPP Investments, General Catalyst, Plural and StepStone, along with current investors: Prima Materia, Accel, and Greenoaks. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In 2025 the firm raised a Series D amount of 600 million, this new financing round thus takes place following that. Investors&#8217; interest in these rounds however out-performed due to increased interest in ai defence tech products.</span></p>
<h2><b>Funding Supports Next Generation Defence Systems</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Helsing plans to deploy the funds for building and embedding new generation AI platforms into defence offerings for its increasingly expanding ecosystem of partner countries. The German firm also designs underwater surveillance capabilities and an AI system capable of sensing, detecting threats and assisting military personnel in challenging operational conditions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">“Software-defined defence is Helsing’s approach combining artificial intelligence with hardware and the latest innovations from the defence domain,” the company noted. “AI helps military forces gain better intelligence about the battlefield and make quicker operational decisions,” it added.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Helsing was founded in 2021 by Dr Gundbert Scherf, Torsten Reil and Niklas Khler and its offerings comprise autonomous defence systems, the battlefield decision-support platform Altra, the loitering munition HX-2 and the autonomous aircraft CA-1 Europa, the company explained.</span></p>
<h2><b>European Defence Technology Attracts Global Investors<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_203514" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-203514" class="size-full wp-image-203514" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/a-futuristic-poster-showcases-a-complex-_qPrHO_2qU8GvH2KMRbgDhQ_yoU8lR0ET3iEhT1MtVdIZg.png" alt="A neon futuristic visual showing a European AI defence network connected across multiple countries." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-203514" class="wp-caption-text">Helsing expands its AI defence ecosystem with strong European roots and growing global investment support. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Although Helsing positions itself as a European defence champion, the latest funding round attracted significant investment from global financial institutions. The company previously stated that it remained around 80% European-owned, despite growing international participation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Helsing currently employs around 900 people across Germany, France, Estonia and the United Kingdom. The company has expanded rapidly alongside increased European defence spending and growing demand for sovereign technology solutions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Its software is already integrated into several military programmes, including systems supplied to Ukraine. Helsing believes governments increasingly want locally developed AI capabilities rather than relying on imported technologies.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/williams-secures-5-34-billion-power-innovation-projects/" data-wpel-link="internal">Williams Secured $5.34 Billion to Expand Power Innovation Projects</a></span></p>
<h2><b>AI Becomes Central to Modern Defence Strategy</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The investment reflects wider momentum across the defence technology industry. Governments are increasing spending on autonomous systems, artificial intelligence and advanced military software as geopolitical tensions continue to reshape security priorities.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Helsing competes with companies such as Anduril in the United States, while also facing emerging European rivals including Quantum Systems and Tekever. However, Helsing has established itself as one of the largest AI-focused defence companies in Europe.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company believes software will become the intelligence layer connecting </span><a href="https://world-warfare-economics.fandom.com/wiki/Military_Asset" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">military assets</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> across air, land, sea and electronic warfare. The new funding gives Helsing additional resources to expand research, strengthen partnerships and deliver AI-powered defence capabilities at greater scale.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/helsing-raises-1-8b-defence-ai-platforms/" data-wpel-link="internal">Helsing Raises $1.8B to Expand European Defence AI Platforms</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
